name: 4-hydroxythreonine-4-phosphate dehydrogenase
classes: Acting on the CH-OH group of donors;
With NAD+ or NADP+ as acceptor
reaction: 4-phosphooxy-L-threonine + NAD+ = 3-amino-2-oxopropyl phosphate + CO2 + NADH + H+ (overall reaction) [RN:R05837]; (1a) 4-phosphooxy-L-threonine + NAD+ = (2S)-2-amino-3-oxo-4-phosphooxybutanoate + NADH + H+ [RN:R05681]; (1b) (2S)-2-amino-3-oxo-4-phosphooxybutanoate = 3-amino-2-oxopropyl phosphate + CO2 (spontaneous) [RN:R07406]
comment: The product of the reaction undergoes decarboxylation to give 3-amino-2-oxopropyl phosphate. The enzyme is part of the biosynthesis pathway of the coenzyme pyridoxal 5'-phosphate found in anaerobic bacteria.
